(74, 'Steve', 'NORTHERN AUSTRALIAN ABORIGINAL CHARITABLE TRUST', 'Darwin,Katherine,Regional Remote Area,Nhulunbuy,Supply Nation Registered', '2019-10-09', '6', '4', 'Un-Verified', 'mr', 'Smith', 'steve.smith@aiggroup.org.au', NULL, '0889222666', '0889222666', '', 'Casuarina', 'NT', 'Po Box 40298', '0810', 'http://aiggroup.org.au/', 'lewis.knibbs@aiggroup.org.au', '0889222666', 'Casuarina', 'NT', NULL, 810, 'Lewis Knibbs', '0477471872', '32 Dripstone Rd', 'lewis.knibbs@aiggroup.org.au', 'NORTHERN AUSTRALIAN ABORIGINAL CHARITABLE TRUST', '31652884437', '', '4', 'y', 'y', 'Darwin,Katherine,Regional Remote Area,Nhulunbuy,Supply Nation Registered', '6', '6', 'Since 1988 Aboriginal Investment Group (AIG) has engaged in the development of Aboriginal communities. We are 100% Aboriginal owned and self-funded. We operate using a unique design of wealth creation and wealth distribution. Our goal is to create wealth through investments and distribute wealth in the form of community projects. We are guided by our strategic objectives:\r\n\r\n•	Economic development in regional and remote Australia. \r\n•	Social dividend and community benefits to regional and remote Aboriginal communities in \r\n        the northern part of the Northern Territory. \r\n•	Ecological development and sustainability in regional and remote Australia.\r\n\r\nAIG manages a large property portfolio and offers a suite of business services. Our select highly qualified team provide business services, utilising client-specific advice and mentoring, which are instrumental to Indigenous corporation’s success. Our current projects include; the construction and management of Indigenous owned remote community stores, management of a tourist park, and providing strategic and governance support to several Indigenous corporations.\r\nWe distribute our wealth through social dividends. Our latest project is the establishment of a commercial laundry in the community of Barunga earlier this year. The goal of the laundry is to tackle disease while creating wealth through Indigenous employment. The laundry provides the opportunity for community members to wash and dry their clothes with specific products that contribute to the reduction in infectious skin diseases. The laundry is run exclusively by five indigenous employee community members. Utilising this business model, AIG will establish another seven laundries in the Top End within the next three years.\r\n', 'Lewis Knibbs', 'Project Manager', 'NORTHERN AUSTRALIAN ABORIGINAL CHARITABLE TRUST', 'https://ntibn.com.au/web/uploadsign/1108313755Signiture.pdf', '', '', '', '2', 'Casuarina', 'Australia ', '0810', '1', 'No', 'No', 'https://ntibn.com.au/web/uploadsign/574715508Signiture.pdf', '2060-01-01', '6', '0', 'NAB Business ', '2', 'Alexa Gutenberger', '2060-01-01', 'Healthcare and Social Assistance', '32 Dripstone Rd', '2000-07-01', 4567, 'Registration', '2060-01-01', 110),
